&lt;p&gt;Phamily, the company&#39;s core technology platform, has transformed chronic disease management with clinically tested AI and easy-to-use technology that enables physicians and care teams to offer high-touch, individualized patient care that has been proven to reduce investment in extra labor and the overall cost of care.&amp;nbsp; Phamily helps ensure healthcare providers are compensated fairly for providing high-quality care between office visits, while improving the lives of patients with chronic diseases. Learn more at phamily.com.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job/Role Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Enterprise Account Executive will be responsible for driving new business growth across large healthcare provider organizations, including health systems, medical groups, and value-based care networks. This role is highly consultative and mission-driven, focused on helping organizations improve clinical outcomes and financial performance through Phamily’s AI-enabled care management platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This individual will own the full sales cycle, from prospecting and qualification through contracting and close, while working closely with marketing, product, clinical, and implementation teams to ensure successful deployment and long-term client value. The Enterprise AE will operate in complex, multi-stakeholder environments and serve as a trusted advisor to executive-level healthcare leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact, high-visibility role that sits at the center of Phamily’s growth strategy and directly contributes to expanding access to proactive, value-based care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full enterprise sales cycle from lead qualification through close across large healthcare provider organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage a pipeline of health systems, medical groups, and value-based care organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute strategic account plans to drive new logo acquisition and revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct executive-level discovery with clinical, operational, and financial stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present Phamily’s value proposition in a consultative, ROI-driven manner tailored to healthcare buyers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product, Clinical, and Implementation teams to ensure smooth handoff post-sale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate complex procurement, contracting, and security review processes within enterprise healthcare systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently meet or exceed quarterly and annual revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
